{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Climate change is already a heavy topic,"},{"time":2000,"text":"and it's getting heavier"},{"time":4000,"text":"because we're understanding"},{"time":6000,"text":"that we need to do more than we are."},{"time":8000,"text":"We're understanding, in fact,"},{"time":10000,"text":"that those of us who live in the developed world"},{"time":12000,"text":"need to be really pushing towards eliminating our emissions."},{"time":15000,"text":"That's, to put it mildly, not what's on the table now."},{"time":18000,"text":"And it tends to feel a little overwhelming"},{"time":20000,"text":"when we look at what is there in reality today"},{"time":23000,"text":"and the magnitude of the problem that we face."},{"time":26000,"text":"And when we have overwhelming problems in front of us,"},{"time":29000,"text":"we tend to seek simple answers."},{"time":32000,"text":"And I think this is what we've done with climate change."},{"time":35000,"text":"We look at where the emissions are coming from --"},{"time":37000,"text":"they're coming out of our tailpipes and smokestacks and so forth,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and we say, okay, well the problem is"},{"time":42000,"text":"that they're coming out of fossil fuels that we're burning,"},{"time":44000,"text":"so therefore, the answer must be"},{"time":47000,"text":"to replace those fossil fuels with clean sources of energy."},{"time":50000,"text":"And while, of course, we do need clean energy,"},{"time":53000,"text":"I would put to you that it's possible"},{"time":55000,"text":"that by looking at climate change"},{"time":57000,"text":"as a clean energy generation problem,"},{"time":59000,"text":"we're in fact setting ourselves up"},{"time":61000,"text":"not to solve it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"And the reason why"},{"time":65000,"text":"is that we live on a planet"},{"time":67000,"text":"that is rapidly urbanizing."},{"time":69000,"text":"That shouldn't be news to any of us."},{"time":71000,"text":"However, it's hard sometimes"},{"time":73000,"text":"to remember the extent of that urbanization."},{"time":76000,"text":"By mid-century,"},{"time":78000,"text":"we're going to have about eight billion -- perhaps more -- people"},{"time":81000,"text":"living in cities or within a day's travel of one."},{"time":84000,"text":"We will be an overwhelmingly urban species."},{"time":87000,"text":"In order to provide"},{"time":89000,"text":"the kind of energy that it would take"},{"time":91000,"text":"for eight billion people living in cities"},{"time":93000,"text":"that are even somewhat like the cities"},{"time":95000,"text":"that those of us in the global North live in today,"},{"time":97000,"text":"we would have to generate"},{"time":99000,"text":"an absolutely astonishing amount of energy."},{"time":101000,"text":"It may be possible"},{"time":103000,"text":"that we are not even able"},{"time":105000,"text":"to build that much clean energy."},{"time":108000,"text":"So if we're seriously talking about tackling climate change"},{"time":111000,"text":"on an urbanizing planet,"},{"time":113000,"text":"we need to look somewhere else for the solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"The solution, in fact, may be closer to hand than we think,"},{"time":119000,"text":"because all of those cities we're building"},{"time":121000,"text":"are opportunities."},{"time":123000,"text":"Every city determines to a very large extent"},{"time":126000,"text":"the amount of energy used by its inhabitants."},{"time":129000,"text":"We tend to think of energy use as a behavioral thing --"},{"time":132000,"text":"I choose to turn this light switch on --"},{"time":134000,"text":"but really, enormous amounts of our energy use"},{"time":137000,"text":"are predestined"},{"time":139000,"text":"by the kinds of communities and cities that we live in."},{"time":142000,"text":"I won't show you very many graphs today,"},{"time":144000,"text":"but if I can just focus on this one for a moment,"},{"time":147000,"text":"it really tells us a lot of what we need to know --"},{"time":149000,"text":"which is, quite simply,"},{"time":151000,"text":"that if you look, for example, at transportation,"},{"time":153000,"text":"a major category of climate emissions,"},{"time":155000,"text":"there is a direct relationship"},{"time":157000,"text":"between how dense a city is"},{"time":159000,"text":"and the amount of climate emissions"},{"time":161000,"text":"that its residents spew out into the air."},{"time":164000,"text":"And the correlation, of course,"},{"time":166000,"text":"is that denser places tend to have lower emissions --"},{"time":169000,"text":"which isn't really all that difficult to figure out, if you think about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"Basically,"},{"time":174000,"text":"we substitute, in our lives,"},{"time":177000,"text":"access to the things we want."},{"time":179000,"text":"We go out there and we hop in our cars"},{"time":181000,"text":"and we drive from place to place."},{"time":183000,"text":"And we're basically using mobility to get the access we need."},{"time":186000,"text":"But when we live in a denser community,"},{"time":188000,"text":"suddenly what we find, of course,"},{"time":190000,"text":"is that the things we need are close by."},{"time":192000,"text":"And since the most sustainable trip"},{"time":194000,"text":"is the one that you never had to make in the first place,"},{"time":197000,"text":"suddenly our lives become instantly more sustainable."},{"time":200000,"text":"And it is possible, of course,"},{"time":202000,"text":"to increase the density of the communities around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"Some places are doing this with new eco districts,"},{"time":207000,"text":"developing whole new sustainable neighborhoods,"},{"time":209000,"text":"which is nice work if you can get it,"},{"time":211000,"text":"but most of the time, what we're talking about is, in fact,"},{"time":214000,"text":"reweaving the urban fabric that we already have."},{"time":216000,"text":"So we're talking about things like infill development:"},{"time":219000,"text":"really sharp little changes"},{"time":221000,"text":"to where we have buildings, where we're developing."},{"time":223000,"text":"Urban retrofitting:"},{"time":225000,"text":"creating different sorts of spaces and uses"},{"time":227000,"text":"out of places that are already there."},{"time":229000,"text":"Increasingly, we're realizing"},{"time":231000,"text":"that we don't even need to densify an entire city."},{"time":234000,"text":"What we need instead is an average density"},{"time":237000,"text":"that rises to a level"},{"time":239000,"text":"where we don't drive as much and so on."},{"time":241000,"text":"And that can be done"},{"time":243000,"text":"by raising the density in very specific spots a whole lot."},{"time":246000,"text":"So you can think of it as tent poles"},{"time":249000,"text":"that actually raise the density of the entire city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"And we find that when we do that,"},{"time":254000,"text":"we can, in fact, have a few places that are really hyper-dense"},{"time":256000,"text":"within a wider fabric of places"},{"time":258000,"text":"that are perhaps a little more comfortable"},{"time":260000,"text":"and achieve the same results."},{"time":262000,"text":"Now we may find that there are places that are really, really dense"},{"time":265000,"text":"and still hold onto their cars,"},{"time":267000,"text":"but the reality is that, by and large,"},{"time":270000,"text":"what we see when we get a lot of people together with the right conditions"},{"time":273000,"text":"is a threshold effect,"},{"time":275000,"text":"where people simply stop driving as much,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and increasingly, more and more people,"},{"time":279000,"text":"if they're surrounded by places that make them feel at home,"},{"time":281000,"text":"give up their cars altogether."},{"time":283000,"text":"And this is a huge, huge energy savings,"},{"time":286000,"text":"because what comes out of our tailpipe"},{"time":288000,"text":"is really just the beginning of the story"},{"time":290000,"text":"with climate emissions from cars."},{"time":292000,"text":"We have the manufacture of the car, the disposal of the car,"},{"time":294000,"text":"all of the parking and freeways and so on."},{"time":297000,"text":"When you can get rid of all of those"},{"time":299000,"text":"because somebody doesn't use any of them really,"},{"time":301000,"text":"you find that you can actually cut transportation emissions"},{"time":303000,"text":"as much as 90 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"And people are embracing this."},{"time":307000,"text":"All around the world, we're seeing more and more people embrace this walkshed life."},{"time":310000,"text":"People are saying that it's moving from the idea of the dream home"},{"time":313000,"text":"to the dream neighborhood."},{"time":315000,"text":"And when you layer that over"},{"time":317000,"text":"with the kind of ubiquitous communications that we're starting to see,"},{"time":320000,"text":"what you find is, in fact,"},{"time":322000,"text":"even more access suffused into spaces."},{"time":325000,"text":"Some of it's transportation access."},{"time":327000,"text":"This is a Mapnificent map that shows me, in this case,"},{"time":330000,"text":"how far I can get from my home in 30 minutes"},{"time":332000,"text":"using public transportation."},{"time":334000,"text":"Some of it is about walking. It's not all perfect yet."},{"time":336000,"text":"This is Google Walking Maps."},{"time":338000,"text":"I asked how to do the greater Ridgeway,"},{"time":340000,"text":"and it told me to go via Guernsey."},{"time":342000,"text":"It did tell me that this route"},{"time":344000,"text":"maybe missing sidewalks or pedestrian paths, though."},{"time":346000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":348000,"text":"But the technologies are getting better,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and we're starting to really kind of crowdsource this navigation."},{"time":352000,"text":"And as we just heard earlier,"},{"time":354000,"text":"of course, we're also learning how to put information on dumb objects."},{"time":357000,"text":"Things that don't have any wiring in them at all,"},{"time":359000,"text":"we're learning how to include"},{"time":361000,"text":"in these systems of notation and navigation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"Part of what we're finding with this"},{"time":366000,"text":"is that what we thought"},{"time":368000,"text":"was the major point"},{"time":370000,"text":"of manufacturing and consumption,"},{"time":373000,"text":"which is to get a bunch of stuff,"},{"time":375000,"text":"is not, in fact,"},{"time":377000,"text":"how we really live best in dense environments."},{"time":379000,"text":"What we're finding is that what we want"},{"time":381000,"text":"is access to the capacities of things."},{"time":383000,"text":"My favorite example is a drill. Who here owns a drill, a home power drill?"},{"time":386000,"text":"Okay. I do too."},{"time":388000,"text":"The average home power drill is used somewhere between six and 20 minutes"},{"time":390000,"text":"in its entire lifetime,"},{"time":392000,"text":"depending on who you ask."},{"time":394000,"text":"And so what we do is we buy these drills"},{"time":397000,"text":"that have a potential capacity of thousands of hours of drill time,"},{"time":400000,"text":"use them once or twice to put a hole in the wall and let them sit."},{"time":403000,"text":"Our cities, I would put to you,"},{"time":405000,"text":"are stockpiles of these surplus capacities."},{"time":408000,"text":"And while we could try and figure out"},{"time":410000,"text":"new ways to use those capacities --"},{"time":412000,"text":"such as cooking or making ice sculptures"},{"time":414000,"text":"or even a mafia hit --"},{"time":416000,"text":"what we probably will find"},{"time":418000,"text":"is that, in fact, turning those products into services"},{"time":420000,"text":"that we have access to when we want them,"},{"time":422000,"text":"is a far smarter way to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"And in fact, even space itself is turning into a service."},{"time":428000,"text":"We're finding that people can share the same spaces,"},{"time":430000,"text":"do stuff with vacant space."},{"time":433000,"text":"Buildings are becoming bundles of services."},{"time":435000,"text":"So we have new designs"},{"time":437000,"text":"that are helping us take mechanical things that we used to spend energy on --"},{"time":440000,"text":"like heating, cooling etc. --"},{"time":442000,"text":"and turn them into things that we avoid spending energy on."},{"time":445000,"text":"So we light our buildings with daylight."},{"time":447000,"text":"We cool them with breezes. We heat them with sunshine."},{"time":450000,"text":"In fact, when we use all these things,"},{"time":452000,"text":"what we've found is that, in some cases,"},{"time":454000,"text":"energy use in a building can drop as much as 90 percent."},{"time":456000,"text":"Which brings on another threshold effect"},{"time":458000,"text":"I like to call furnace dumping,"},{"time":460000,"text":"which is, quite simply,"},{"time":462000,"text":"if you have a building that doesn't need to be heated with a furnace,"},{"time":464000,"text":"you save a whole bunch of money up front."},{"time":466000,"text":"These things actually become cheaper to build"},{"time":468000,"text":"than the alternatives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"Now when we look at being able"},{"time":473000,"text":"to slash our product use, slash our transportation use,"},{"time":476000,"text":"slash our building energy use,"},{"time":478000,"text":"all of that is great, but it still leaves something behind."},{"time":481000,"text":"And if we're going to really, truly become sustainable cities,"},{"time":483000,"text":"we need to think a little differently."},{"time":485000,"text":"This is one way to do it."},{"time":487000,"text":"This is Vancouver's propaganda about how green a city they are."},{"time":489000,"text":"And certainly lots of people have taken to heart"},{"time":491000,"text":"this idea that a sustainable city is covered in greenery."},{"time":494000,"text":"So we have visions like this."},{"time":496000,"text":"We have visions like this. We have visions like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499000,"text":"Now all of these are fine projects,"},{"time":501000,"text":"but they really have missed an essential point,"},{"time":504000,"text":"which is it's not about the leaves above,"},{"time":506000,"text":"it's about the systems below."},{"time":508000,"text":"Do they, for instance, capture rainwater"},{"time":510000,"text":"so that we can reduce water use?"},{"time":512000,"text":"Water is energy intensive."},{"time":515000,"text":"Do they, perhaps, include green infrastructure,"},{"time":517000,"text":"so that we can take runoff"},{"time":519000,"text":"and water that's going out of our houses"},{"time":521000,"text":"and clean it and filter it"},{"time":523000,"text":"and grow urban street trees?"},{"time":525000,"text":"Do they connect us back to the ecosystems around us"},{"time":528000,"text":"by, for example, connecting us to rivers"},{"time":530000,"text":"and allowing for restoration?"},{"time":532000,"text":"Do they allow for pollination,"},{"time":534000,"text":"pollinator pathways"},{"time":536000,"text":"that bees and butterflies and such can come back into our cities?"},{"time":539000,"text":"Do they even take the very waste matter"},{"time":541000,"text":"that we have from food and fiber and so forth,"},{"time":544000,"text":"and turn it back into soil"},{"time":546000,"text":"and sequester carbon --"},{"time":548000,"text":"take carbon out of the air"},{"time":550000,"text":"in the process of using our cities?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"I would submit to you that all of these things are not only possible,"},{"time":555000,"text":"they're being done right now,"},{"time":557000,"text":"and that it's a darn good thing."},{"time":559000,"text":"Because right now, our economy by and large"},{"time":562000,"text":"operates as Paul Hawken said,"},{"time":564000,"text":"\"by stealing the future, selling it in the present"},{"time":566000,"text":"and calling it GDP.\""},{"time":568000,"text":"And if we have another eight billion"},{"time":570000,"text":"or seven billion,"},{"time":572000,"text":"or six billion, even, people,"},{"time":574000,"text":"living on a planet where their cities also steal the future,"},{"time":577000,"text":"we're going to run out of future really fast."},{"time":579000,"text":"But if we think differently,"},{"time":581000,"text":"I think that, in fact, we can have cities"},{"time":583000,"text":"that are not only zero emissions,"},{"time":585000,"text":"but have unlimited possibilities as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}